### Folder & File Structure
This is the recommended project folder structure:
- src/
  - assets/        → Static files (images, SVGs, fonts, etc.)
  - commons/       → Reusable, generic components or utilities shared across features
  - components/    → Feature-specific UI components, organized by domain or module
  - constants/     → Global constants and configuration values
  - context/       → React Contexts for app-wide state (used sparingly)
  - hocs/          → Higher-Order Components
  - hooks/         → Reusable custom hooks (shared across the app)
  - pages/         → Next.js page components (uses file-based routing)
  - stores/        → Application state management (e.g., Tanstack/store)

### Feature-Based Folder Structure Convention
For each component/feature, follow this structure:
src/components/
  └── FeatureName/
        ├── FeatureName.tsx             → Main presentation component (UI only)
        ├── FeatureName.styled.tsx      → Tailwind-based styled components
        ├── useFeatureName.ts           → Encapsulated logic (e.g., state, events, effects)
        ├── FeatureName.d.ts            → Local types/interfaces
        └── index.ts                    → Re-export component & types (optional)
        └── FeatureName.constants.ts    → Constants of the folder



